3 groups of skiers- 2 jet skis- bays weedy.
Algae- green stuff floating in water.
Lots of skiers- 18 loons in 2 groups on 13th- lots of gulls- duck adopted loon chick- water snake near boat landing.
Lake has been very rough lately- stirring up the water- mostly sunny- air temp: 70 degrees.
Weather has been terrible- since the last reading.
Partly sunny- wind is calm- weather is terrible and the wind is making lake turbid.
Partly sunny and 70 degrees.  Wind is calm.
Wind is moderate- mostly sunny and 68 degrees.
Partly sunny and 72 degrees.  Wind is calm.  Bloom has started on the lake.
Algae is becoming more noticeable- mostly sunny + 79 F.
Mostly sunny and 65 degrees.  Lake is a strange looking brown.
Mostly sunny with some haze.  The lake doesn't look too bad.
Sunny- 60 degrees- light wind- algae level has noticeably increased.
Very windy- sunny- hazy- air temp 82- best reading of this year so far
Air temp 74- partly sunny- light wind- beautiful day.
Mostly sunny- air temp 85- light wind.
Heavy use- 3-4 skiers daily and jet skis- fishermen are causing turbidity.
Sunny with a temperature of 75 degrees.  Some thick globs of green algae on the lake.
Partly sunny- light wind.  Had thunderstorm this A.M. which may affect reading.
Partly sunny- temp. 68 F.  Algae is very thick.
Partly sunny 70 degrees F.  Algae is partly sunny 70 degrees F.  Algae is just about gone from surface.
Mostly sunny.  75 degrees F- still some traces of algae.
Slight haze- but very nice.  Temp. 78 degrees F.  Crayfish have become very active + we have a lot of them.
90 degrees F- hot * humid.  Even crayfish are hiding- but they're still here.
84 degrees F- slight overcast + mild wind.
77 degrees F -sunny- mild wind- algae is here.  A lot of crayfish-can you help with crayfish  * (sent note to Laura 8/31).
Sunny + 55 degrees F- algae is getting pretty thick.
Water too cold for swimming.  Mostly sunny + 54 degrees F.  Lake water is very green.  This is our last reading for the year.  See you next year.  Happy holidays.
Mostly sunny 70 degrees- first reading of the year because of weather-rain and wind.  Not sign of algae yet.
Mostly sunny-80 degrees F.  Water looks good.  Lots of boat traffic.
Sunny and 75 degrees.  Algae really getting thick.  Crayfish are abundant.
Sunny and 75 degrees.  Algae is thick- lots of crayfish.
45 degrees F- sunny. Algae is very thick. Went out to get several readings this year but water too rough at sample area.
Mostly sunny- 76 degrees.  Crabs are in abundance.  Water is clear black.
78 degrees- partly cloudy- light wind- algae is starting to bloom.
78 degrees- partly sunny- slight breeze.  Algae not too bad.
70 F. Mostly sunny + windy. Water not as clear as last time.
75 F- mostly sunny and windy.  Algae getting thicker.
50 F. Cloudy with rain. Last report for year.
78 degrees F and partly sunny.  First decent day we are able to take a reading for this year.
80 degrees F- sunny- and heavy boat traffic.
77 degrees F- mostly sunny- and algae starting to get thicker.
68 degrees F- mostly cloudy- and algae is really thick.
Partly sunny and very active boat traffic.
Sunny- 4" lake ripple- lake in full bloom- day after a 2" rain.
Very bright- no clouds- 6" lake ripple- bloom on decline- and water is cooling.
Overcast-  no sun- slight wind - south
Overcast- light rain- choppy- bloom less.
Cloudy- strong W wind- whitecaps.  Have had several windy days.
Overcast with drizzle.  N wind.  Near whitecaps.
Sun- N wind- small waves - chop.
Sun with slight chop - SE wind
Sun with brisk chop- NW wind
Sun with chop on SW wind
Had 7" of rain since 10/3/05.  Sun- SE wind- chop
clouds- NW- white caps- 12"-14" waves- week of strong winds
sunny- E wind- w/slight chop- past 4th week- much boat traffic
bright sun- calm- hot for last 10 days
bright sun- N wind w/8-10" waves
Sun-  no clouds.  Wind east 10-15 mph.  6-10" waves.
Sun- few clouds.  Wind calm.  1/2" rain 8 hr before reading.
Some sun- NW wind w/ 18" white caps.
Partly cloudy- sun- slight breeze.  Small ripple.
Sunny- slight ripple.  Very few clouds.  Took additional reading at 1 PM;  Cloudy- west wind with 6" waves.  Secchi 4.0 feet- did not hit bottom- lake level normal- murky- brown- pereception 3.
Cloudy- slight chop.  S. wind. Cloudy- slight chop.  S wind.
Overcast- calm- lake surface with algae in full bloom. Overcast- calm- lake surface with algae in full bloom.
Overcast- SW wind w/ 6" waves.  Pools of surface algae in bays on 25th.
Overcast- W wind with 6" waves.  Received 3.5" rain.
Sunny- S wind with 3" waves.  Last 3 days were 70 F with 1.5" rain.
Sun- E wind with 3-4" waves.  2 cold windy days.
Helper Pete Larson.  Lake level high. Weather Clear/Sunny. Slight wind.Lake appearance Murky green Helper Peter Larson - Lake level high- Weather Clear/Sunny- Slight wind- Lake appearance murky green
Checking DO meter- Cloudy- windy- rain within last 24 hours- temp hi 60's
Secci reading only- Day was partly sunny- light breeze- rain in previous 24 hours about 1/2 inch
Negligible rain last three days- Windy- 4-6 in chop on water
Partly Sunny- 3 in chop- little rain in last 3 days
Temp 70 degrees F- LIght wind- sunny few clouds-
Clear- partly cloudy sky- 3-4In. Chop- Cleqar green water color
10 mph wind- 3-6 inch chop- party sunny- 3/4in.  rain in last 72 hours
Ptly cloudy- 3-4 in. chop no rain in last 72 hours
Sunny - light wind- water level is spring normal
Sunny/partly cloudy- 1/2 in rain in last 48 hours- slight chop on water

Partly cloudy- rain last tow days was 7/8 in. Light breeze and light chop on water Partly cloudy- rain last tow days was 7/8 in. Light breeze and light chop on water Partly cloudy- rain last two days was 7/8 in. Light breeze and light chop on water Partly cloudy- rain last two days was 7/8 in. Light breeze and light chop on water Partly cloudy- rain last two days was 7/8 in. Light breeze and light chop on water Partly cloudy- rain last two days was 7/8 in. Light breeze and light chop on water Partly cloudy- rain last two days was 7/8 in. Light breeze and light chop on water Partly cloudy- rain last two days was 7/8 in. Light breeze and light chop on water Partly cloudy- rain last two days was 7/8 in. Light breeze and light chop on water
Slightly cloudy- windy previous few days- Rain about 1 1/2 inch in previous 6 days
Weather is cloudy and misty. the last 4 days have been very windy and cloudy
Sunny w/ few clouds- slight breeze windy yesterday.
Sunny- partly cloudy windy last 3 days
partly cloudy- light wind- 1/5 in rain in last 24 hours
Sunny parlt cloudy- slight wind. heavy rain in last 6 days
sunny skies- no rain in last 6 days
40 deg- sunny- no prec for last month- windy last few days
Cloudy- rain within last 3 days- slight breeze
First testing of the season. Secchi only/ lake hasn't cleared as nornal for spring/ water is somewhat murky/ temp in the 60's
Clear w/ temps in the 60's   Clear w/ temps in the 60's
Cloudy- lite wind following a week of high winds
More then 4 1/2 inches of rain in last 7 days. Substantial algae has developed in last two weeks.
Sunny- no rain for last 5 days
water sampled but Oxygen sensor doesn't work . needs repair
Roger Skoletski took me out in his boat.
Cool- Air Temp was 55 degrees F.
sunny/few clouds calm after two days of wind
